{{Lunisolar May}} '''May 28''' is the 28th day of the month {{ill|May (Lunisolar)|ja|5月 (旧暦)|lt=May|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, the 5th month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}. Its {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} day is {{ill|Tomobiki|ja|友引|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}.
== Events == * {{ill|Kenkyū|ja|建久|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 4th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1193]] {{ill|June 28|ja|6月28日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – The brothers {{ill|Soga Yūsēi|ja|曾我祐成|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} and {{ill|Soga Tokitomi|ja|曾我時致|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} avenged their father, {{ill|Kawazu Yūtai|ja|河津祐泰|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, by killing their enemy, {{ill|Kudō Yūkine|ja|工藤祐経|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, during the conflict known as {{ill|Genkō no Ran|ja|元弘の乱|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://example.com|title=Reference needed|accessdate=2021-04}}</ref> * {{ill|Genna|ja|元和|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 1st year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1615]] {{ill|June 1|ja|6月1日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – The shogun, {{ill|Tokugawa Ieyasu|ja|徳川家康|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, mobilized his forces to confront the situation during the summer siege of Osaka. * {{ill|Tenmei|ja|天保|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 6th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1786]] {{ill|June 1|ja|6月1日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – Under orders from the Tokugawa shogunate, the commander {{ill|Saigō Tokunai|ja|最上徳内|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} landed on 【Oki Province】 (隠岐) to secure the area. == Births == * {{ill|Gen'ei|ja|元永|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 2nd year ({{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1119]] {{ill|July 7|ja|7月7日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Tendoku Tennō|ja|崇徳天皇|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, the 75th Emperor of Japan (died [[1164]]). * {{ill|Hōreki|ja|宝暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 4th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1754]] {{ill|July 18|ja|7月18日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Kuroda Harutaka|ja|黒田治高|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, the 8th lord of the Fukuoka Domain (died [[1782]]). * {{ill|Tenpō|ja|天保|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 5th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1834]] {{ill|July 4|ja|7月4日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Katsura Hisatake|ja|桂久武|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, a politician (died [[1877]]). * {{ill|Kōka|ja|弘化|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 4th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1847]] {{ill|July 10|ja|7月10日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Monoatsukami Takami|ja|物集高見|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, a scholar of national literature (died [[1928]]). * {{ill|Kaei|ja|嘉永|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 3rd year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1850]] {{ill|July 7|ja|7月7日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – The first generation of the rakugo performer {{ill|Sanyūtei En'yū|ja|三遊亭圓遊|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, a famed storyteller (died [[1907]]).
== Deaths == * [[Gangyō]] 4th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[880]] {{ill|July 9|ja|7月9日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Ariwara no Narihira|ja|在原業平|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, a renowned waka poet and one of the Six Immortals of Poetry (born [[825]]). * {{ill|Kenkyū|ja|建久|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 4th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1193]] {{ill|June 28|ja|6月28日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Soga Yūsēi|ja|曾我祐成|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, a samurai and elder brother among the Soga brothers (born [[1172]]). * [[Keichō]] 20th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1615]] {{ill|June 24|ja|6月24日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Katagiri Kagetora|ja|片桐且元|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, a daimyō (born [[1556]]).
