== Events == * [[:en:Kenkyū|Kenkyū]] 4th year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:1193|1193]] [[:en:June 28|June 28]]) – The brothers [[:en:Soga Sukenari|Soga Yūsēi]] and [[:en:Soga Tokimune|Soga Tokitomi]] avenged their father, [[:en:Kawazu Sukeyasu|Kawazu Yūtai]], by killing their enemy, [[:en:Kudō Suketsune|Kudō Yūkine]], during the conflict known as [[:en:Genkō War|Genkō no Ran]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://example.com|title=Reference needed|accessdate=2021-04|qq=}}</ref> * [[:en:Yuanhe|Genna]] 1st year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1615|1615]] [[:en:June 1|June 1]]) – The shogun, [[:en:Tokugawa Ieyasu|Tokugawa Ieyasu]], mobilized his forces to confront the situation during the summer siege of Osaka. * [[:en:Tenpō|Tenmei]] 6th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1786|1786]] [[:en:June 1|June 1]]) – Under orders from the Tokugawa shogunate, the commander [[:en:Mogami Tokunai|Saigō Tokunai]] landed on 【Oki Province】 (隠岐) to secure the area. == Births == * [[:en:Gen'ei|Gen'ei]] 2nd year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:1119|1119]] [[:en:July 7|July 7]]) – [[:en:Emperor Sutoku|Tendoku Tennō]], the 75th Emperor of Japan (died [[:en:1164|1164]]). * [[:en:Hōreki|Hōreki]] 4th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1754|1754]] [[:en:July 18|July 18]]) – {{ill|Kuroda Harutaka|ja|黒田治高|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kuroda Harutaka|qq=}}, the 8th lord of the Fukuoka Domain (died [[:en:1782|1782]]). * [[:en:Tenpō|Tenpō]] 5th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1834|1834]] [[:en:July 4|July 4]]) – {{ill|Katsura Hisatake|ja|桂久武|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Katsura Hisatake|qq=}}, a politician (died [[:en:1877|1877]]). * [[:en:Kōka|Kōka]] 4th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1847|1847]] [[:en:July 10|July 10]]) – {{ill|Monoatsukami Takami|ja|物集高見|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Monoatsukami Takami|qq=}}, a scholar of national literature (died [[1928]]). * [[:en:Kaei|Kaei]] 3rd year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1850|1850]] [[:en:July 7|July 7]]) – The first generation of the rakugo performer {{ill|Sanyūtei En'yū|ja|三遊亭圓遊|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sanyūtei En'yū|qq=}}, a famed storyteller (died [[:en:1907|1907]]).
== Deaths == * [[Gangyō]] 4th year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[880]] [[:en:July 9|July 9]]) – [[:en:Ariwara no Narihira|Ariwara no Narihira]], a renowned waka poet and one of the Six Immortals of Poetry (born [[825]]). * [[:en:Kenkyū|Kenkyū]] 4th year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:1193|1193]] [[:en:June 28|June 28]]) – [[:en:Soga Sukenari|Soga Yūsēi]], a samurai and elder brother among the Soga brothers (born [[:en:1172|1172]]). * [[Keichō]] 20th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1615|1615]] [[:en:June 24|June 24]]) – [[:en:Katagiri Katsumoto|Katagiri Kagetora]], a daimyō (born [[:en:1556|1556]]).
