lar of national literature (died [[:en:1928|1928]]). * [[:en:Kaei|Kaei]] 3rd year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1850|1850]] [[:en:July 7|July 7]]) – The first generation of the rakugo performer {{ill|Sanyūtei En'yū|ja|三遊亭圓遊|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sanyūtei En'yū|qq=}}, a famed storyteller (died [[:en:1907|1907]]).
== Deaths == * [[Gangyō]] 4th year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:880|880]] [[:en:July 9|July 9]]) – [[:en:Ariwara no Narihira|Ariwara no Narihira]], a renowned waka poet and one of the Six Immortals of Poetry (born [[:en:825|825]]). * [[:en:Kenkyū|Kenkyū]] 4th year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:1193|1193]] [[:en:June 28|June 28]]) – [[:en:Soga Sukenari|Soga Yūsēi]], a samurai and elder brother among the Soga brothers (born [[:en:1172|1172]]). * [[Keichō]] 20th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1615|1615]] [[:en:June 24|June 24]]) – [[:en:Katagiri Katsumoto|Katagiri Kagetora]], a daimyō (born [[:en:1556|1556]]).
