'''May 28''' is the 28th day of the month {{ill|May (Lunisolar)|ja|5月 (旧暦)|lt=May (Satsuki)|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/May (Lunisolar)|qq=}}, the 5th month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=}}. Its {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Rokuyō|qq=}} day is {{ill|Tomobiki|qid=Q96759840|1=tomobiki}}{{efn|ja|友引|1=Rokuyō|comment=changed title based on wikidata|qid=Q9418169}}{{efn|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tomobiki|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 六曜|1=Rokuyō|comment=changed title based on wikidata|qid=Q9418169}}.

== Events ==
* {{ill|Kenkyū|en|Kenkyū|qid=Q1193933|lt=Kenkyū|1=Kenkyū}} 4th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|en|Julian calendar|qid=Q11184|lt=Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar}} {{ill|1193|en|1193|qid=Q19741|lt=1193|1=1193}} {{ill|June 28|en|June 28|qid=Q2660|lt=June 28|1=June 28}}) – The brothers {{ill|Soga Sukenari|en|Soga Sukenari|qid=Q11515406|lt=Soga Yūsēi|1=Soga Sukenari}} and {{ill|Soga Tokimune|en|Soga Tokimune|qid=Q11515401|lt=Soga Tokitomi|1=Soga Tokimune}} avenged their father, {{ill|Kawazu Sukeyasu|en|Kawazu Sukeyasu|qid=Q11553998|lt=Kawazu Yūtai|1=Kawazu Sukeyasu}}, by killing their enemy, {{ill|Kudō Suketsune|en|Kudō Suketsune|qid=Q11479615|lt=Kudō Yūkine|1=Kudō Suketsune}}, during the conflict known as {{ill|Genkō War|en|Genkō War|qid=Q1432624|lt=Genkō no Ran|1=Genkō War}}.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://example.com|title=Reference needed|accessdate=2021-04|qq=}}</ref>
* {{ill|Yuanhe|en|Yuanhe|qid=Q10889567|lt=Genna|1=Yuanhe}} 1st year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|qid=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}} {{ill|1615|en|1615|qid=Q6784|lt=1615|1=1615}} {{ill|June 1|en|June 1|qid=Q2625|lt=June 1|1=June 1}}) – The shogun, {{ill|Tokugawa Ieyasu|en|Tokugawa Ieyasu|qid=Q171977|lt=Tokugawa Ieyasu|1=Tokugawa Ieyasu}}, mobilized his forces to confront the situation during the summer siege of Osaka.
* {{ill|Tenpō|en|Tenpō|qid=Q1369045|lt=Tenmei|1=Tenpō}} 6th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|qid=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}} {{ill|1786|en|1786|qid=Q7760|lt=1786|1=1786}} {{ill|June 1|en|June 1|qid=Q2625|lt=June 1|1=June 1}}) – Under orders from the Tokugawa shogunate, the commander {{ill|Mogami Tokunai|en|Mogami Tokunai|qid=Q4141812|lt=Saigō Tokunai|1=Mogami Tokunai}} landed on 【Oki Province】 (隠岐) to secure the area.
== Births ==
* {{ill|Gen'ei|en|Gen'ei|qid=Q1193613|lt=Gen'ei|1=Gen'ei}} 2nd year ({{ill|Julian calendar|en|Julian calendar|qid=Q11184|lt=Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar}} {{ill|1119|en|1119|qid=Q19540|lt=1119|1=1119}} {{ill|July 7|en|July 7|qid=Q2694|lt=July 7|1=July 7}}) – {{ill|Emperor Sutoku|en|Emperor Sutoku|qid=Q349287|lt=Tendoku Tennō|1=Emperor Sutoku}}, the 75th Emperor of Japan (died {{ill|1164|en|1164|qid=Q19674|lt=1164|1=1164}}).
* {{ill|Hōreki|en|Hōreki|qid=Q1194397|lt=Hōreki|1=Hōreki}} 4th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|qid=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}} {{ill|1754|en|1754|qid=Q7623|lt=1754|1=1754}} {{ill|July 18|en|July 18|qid=Q2730|lt=July 18|1=July 18}}) – {{ill|Kuroda Harutaka|ja|黒田治高|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kuroda Harutaka|1=Q11678626|comment=changed title based on wikidata|qid=Q11678626}}, the 8th lord of the Fukuoka Domain (died {{ill|1782|en|1782|qid=Q7740|lt=1782|1=1782}}).
* {{ill|Tenpō|en|Tenpō|qid=Q1369045|lt=Tenpō|1=Tenpō}} 5th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|qid=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}} {{ill|1834|en|1834|qid=Q7591|lt=1834|1=1834}} {{ill|July 4|en|July 4|qid=Q2698|lt=July 4|1=July 4}}) – {{ill|Katsura Hisatake|ja|桂久武|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Katsura Hisatake|1=Katsura Hisatake|comment=changed title based on wikidata|qid=Q11162562}}, a politician (died {{ill|1877|en|1877|qid=Q7773|lt=1877|1=1877}}).
* {{ill|Kōka|en|Kōka|qid=Q1325317|lt=Kōka|1=Kōka}} 4th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|qid=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}} {{ill|1847|en|1847|qid=Q7644|lt=1847|1=1847}} {{ill|July 10|en|July 10|qid=Q2689|lt=July 10|1=July 10}}) – {{ill|Monoatsukami Takami|ja|物集高見|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Monoatsukami Takami|1=Mozume Takami|comment=changed title based on wikidata|qid=Q6537728}}, a scholar of national literature (died {{ill|1928|en|1928|qid=Q19715|lt=1928|1=1928}}).
* {{ill|Kaei|en|Kaei|qid=Q1146125|lt=Kaei|1=Kaei}} 3rd year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|qid=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}} {{ill|1850|en|1850|qid=Q7653|lt=1850|1=1850}} {{ill|July 7|en|July 7|qid=Q2694|lt=July 7|1=July 7}}) – The first generation of the rakugo performer {{ill|Sanyūtei En'yū|ja|三遊亭圓遊|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sanyūtei En'yū|1=En'yū San'yūtei|comment=changed title based on wikidata|qid=Q11357497}}, a famed storyteller (died {{ill|1907|en|1907|qid=Q2048|lt=1907|1=1907}}).

== Deaths ==
* {{ill|Gangyō|en|Gangyō|qid=Q747451|lt=Gangyō|1=Gangyō}} 4th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|en|Julian calendar|qid=Q11184|lt=Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar}} {{ill|880|en|880|qid=Q23618|lt=880|1=880}} {{ill|July 9|en|July 9|qid=Q2690|lt=July 9|1=July 9}}) – {{ill|Ariwara no Narihira|en|Ariwara no Narihira|qid=Q451991|lt=Ariwara no Narihira|1=Ariwara no Narihira}}, a renowned waka poet and one of the Six Immortals of Poetry (born {{ill|825|en|825|qid=Q24624|lt=825|1=825}}).
* {{ill|Kenkyū|en|Kenkyū|qid=Q1193933|lt=Kenkyū|1=Kenkyū}} 4th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|en|Julian calendar|qid=Q11184|lt=Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar}} {{ill|1193|en|1193|qid=Q19741|lt=1193|1=1193}} {{ill|June 28|en|June 28|qid=Q2660|lt=June 28|1=June 28}}) – {{ill|Soga Sukenari|en|Soga Sukenari|qid=Q11515406|lt=Soga Yūsēi|1=Soga Sukenari}}, a samurai and elder brother among the Soga brothers (born {{ill|1172|en|1172|qid=Q19687|lt=1172|1=1172}}).
* {{ill|Keichō|en|Keichō|qid=Q1328185|lt=Keichō|1=Keichō}} 20th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|qid=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}} {{ill|1615|en|1615|qid=Q6784|lt=1615|1=1615}} {{ill|June 24|en|June 24|qid=Q2665|lt=June 24|1=June 24}}) – {{ill|Katagiri Katsumoto|en|Katagiri Katsumoto|qid=Q1882775|lt=Katagiri Kagetora|1=Katagiri Katsumoto}}, a daimyō (born {{ill|1556|en|1556|qid=Q6590|lt=1556|1=1556}}).

